---
alwaysApply: true
---

- This is a Next.js 15 project using the App Router, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS
- Always use the app/ directory structure, never pages/
- Never use inline styles unless a value cannot be expressed in Tailwind (e.g. exact hex colors, dynamic opacity). Prefer Tailwind classes for everything else
- Brand colors: #315798 (primary blue), #7D95E0 (accent blue), #D4A791 (terracotta — ledger, history, permanence). Background: #0a0f1a. Cold card surfaces: #0d0a0a. Warm card surfaces: #1a120e
- Terracotta (#D4A791) is never decorative. Use it only on meaningful elements: evidence, history, permanence, the Avera core thesis
- Section pills always use #7D95E0. Never terracotta on pills
- Card borders are always rgba(212,167,145,0.35) — terracotta on all cards, both cold and warm
- All components go in app/components/
- All pages go in app/ as page.tsx files
- Never install unnecessary dependencies. Ask before adding any new package
- Always use TypeScript, never plain JavaScript
- Keep components small and single-purpose
- The site is dark mode only. Never add light mode styles
- Never touch globals.css unless explicitly asked
- No em dashes anywhere in copy. Use periods, commas, colons, or semicolons instead
- Write "Zero cloud storage" not "zero cloud dependency"
- No autonomous AI framing. AI observes and informs, never acts
- ConstellationBackground.tsx is the canvas animation component. Do not rename or restructure it
- Footer section headers are terracotta. Bottom tagline is #7D95E0
- Navbar: Sign Up button uses terracotta bg. Active nav link uses terracotta underline
- All Composer prompts must be inside a code block, no exceptions
- One problem per prompt. Do not combine fixes with refactors
- Never suggest changes to files you haven't been shown